{
  "page": "Amory Lorch",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">\"Amory\" redirects here. For the Kingsguard under King Aegon III Targaryen, see <a href=\"/index.php/Amaury_Peake\" title=\"Amaury Peake\">Amaury Peake</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lorch\" title=\"House Lorch\"><img alt=\"House Lorch.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/05/House_Lorch.png/50px-House_Lorch.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/05/House_Lorch.png/75px-House_Lorch.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/05/House_Lorch.png/100px-House_Lorch.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Amory Lorch</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lorch\" title=\"House Lorch\"><img alt=\"House Lorch.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/05/House_Lorch.png/50px-House_Lorch.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/05/House_Lorch.png/75px-House_Lorch.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/05/House_Lorch.png/100px-House_Lorch.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Lorch.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Lorch.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/ac/Lorch.jpg/350px-Lorch.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" srcset=\"/images/a/ac/Lorch.jpg 1.5x\" /></a><div>Amory Lorch, by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://en.amokanet.ru/gallery/martin/\">Amok©</a></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe manticore<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">Castellan</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lorch\" title=\"House Lorch\">House Lorch</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nor before <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_246_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">246&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">Westerlands</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafamory_lorch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafamory_lorch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/299_AC\" title=\"299 AC\">299&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fintan_McKeown\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fintan McKeown\">Fintan McKeown</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_2\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 2\">Season 2</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Amory Lorch</b> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lorch\" title=\"House Lorch\">House Lorch</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Bannerman\" title=\"Bannerman\">bannerman</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>, Amory is portrayed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fintan_McKeown\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fintan McKeown\">Fintan McKeown</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Amory\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Amory</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Amory\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Amory</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Amory_Lorch\" title=\"Category:Images of Amory Lorch\">Images of Amory Lorch</a></div>\n<p>Ser Amory is a stout man with a piggy face,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> little pig's eyes,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and a high, thin voice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The knight is regarded as a cruel and unintelligent, brutal man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> He is the sort of man to order the deaths of non-combatants as if it bores him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Amory's <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">breastplate</a> is decorated with ornate scrollwork,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and a <a href=\"/index.php/Manticore\" title=\"Manticore\">manticore</a> is depicted on his shield.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> His <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">warhorse</a> is armored.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to a semi-canon source, during the <a href=\"/index.php/Reyne-Tarbeck_rebellion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion\">Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/261_AC\" title=\"261 AC\">261&#160;AC</a>, Ser Amory threw the <a href=\"/index.php/Last_Lord_Tarbeck\" title=\"Last Lord Tarbeck\">last Lord Tarbeck</a>, a three-year-old boy, down a well in <a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a>. It is disputed whether this was done per the orders of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>, or without his knowledge.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/283_AC\" title=\"283 AC\">283&#160;AC</a>, Amory was responsible for the murder of the three-year old Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Rhaegar)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Sack_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Sack of King&#39;s Landing\">Sack of King's Landing</a>. Per the order of Tywin Lannister, Amory and <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> scaled the walls of <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor%27s_Holdfast\" title=\"Maegor&#39;s Holdfast\">Maegor's Holdfast</a> to access the royal apartments.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> Alongside and in front of several <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Men-at-arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Men-at-arms\">men-at-arms</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> he dragged the screaming toddler from under her father <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaegar Targaryen\">Rhaegar's</a> bed, and when she kicked him, stabbed her dozens of times.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_Amory_Lorch_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e0/Ser_Amory_Lorch_TheMico.jpg/350px-Ser_Amory_Lorch_TheMico.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"495\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/e/e0/Ser_Amory_Lorch_TheMico.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_Amory_Lorch_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Amory, by The Mico</div></div></div>\n<p>At the onset of the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/299_AC\" title=\"299 AC\">299&#160;AC</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> orders his brother, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan</a>, to direct Ser Amory, along with his fellow bannerman Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellsword</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Vargo_Hoat\" title=\"Vargo Hoat\">Vargo Hoat</a>, to forage the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and to burn what he does not take. Each of the raider captains is to have three hundred cavalry.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>At a <a href=\"/index.php/Holdfast\" title=\"Holdfast\">holdfast</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye_town\" title=\"Gods Eye town\">a town</a> by the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye\" title=\"Gods Eye\">Gods Eye</a>, Amory's raiding party encounters <a href=\"/index.php/Yoren\" title=\"Yoren\">Yoren</a>'s group of recruits for the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>, with <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> hidden among them. Even though the Watch takes no part in the wars of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>, Amory orders his men-at-arms to storm the holdfast,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and Yoren is killed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Fight_at_the_holdfast\" title=\"Fight at the holdfast\">fight at the holdfast</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> Because of Yoren's fate, Arya adds Amory's name to the <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark#Arya.27s_prayer\" title=\"Arya Stark\">list of people she wants to kill</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> Amory departs the town without burying any of the dead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Amory captures two innocent <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a>, a beekeeper and his wife, and threatens far and wide to hang them if Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Beric_Dondarrion\" title=\"Beric Dondarrion\">Beric Dondarrion</a> does not surrender to him. When Beric surrenders, Amory hangs the beekeeper and his wife anyway, with Beric strung up in the middle. Beric is later resurrected by <a href=\"/index.php/Thoros_of_Myr\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thoros of Myr\">Thoros of Myr</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Arya Stark, disguised as a servant in <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, is offered the deaths of three people by <a href=\"/index.php/Jaqen_H%27ghar\" title=\"Jaqen H&#39;ghar\">Jaqen H'ghar</a>. She considers Amory for one of them, before deciding on <a href=\"/index.php/Chiswyck\" title=\"Chiswyck\">Chiswyck</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> takes the majority of his army east to engage <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>, he makes Amory <a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">castellan</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, with the <a href=\"/index.php/Bloody_Mummers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bloody Mummers\">Bloody Mummers</a> also left behind to do the foraging.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> While castellan, Amory resides in the castellan's chambers in <a href=\"/index.php/Kingspyre_Tower\" title=\"Kingspyre Tower\">Kingspyre Tower</a>, with only a hundred men left to guard the rest of Harrenhal,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and drinks a great deal of the best <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a> in the castle's cellars.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Amory is eventually captured by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a>, after Roose persuades <a href=\"/index.php/Vargo_Hoat\" title=\"Vargo Hoat\">Vargo Hoat</a> to betray <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> and to seize control of the castle. After the <a href=\"/index.php/Fall_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Fall of Harrenhal\">fall of Harrenhal</a>, Amory is paraded naked before Roose and Vargo. As he pleads and sobs, he is kicked into the <a href=\"/index.php/Bear\" title=\"Bear\">bear</a> pit to be killed by the bear inside it. Arya Stark is present to witness Amory's death, and mentally notes, \"The bear is all in black. Like Yoren.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The bear tears Amory apart.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> finds a human jawbone in the bear pit of Harrenhal. As it still has maggoty flesh on it, it may have been Amory's.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a> comes to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to seek justice for the deaths of his sister Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Martell\" title=\"Elia Martell\">Elia</a> and her children, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Rhaegar)\">Rhaenys</a> and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (son of Rhaegar)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, during the <a href=\"/index.php/Sack_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Sack of King&#39;s Landing\">Sack of King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> tells his son <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion</a> his plan to blame all three of the deaths entirely on the deceased Amory (who in truth had only killed Rhaenys), to circumvent giving Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> over to Oberyn. According to Tywin, Amory justified his brutal murder of Rhaenys because the screaming child had kicked him. Tywin plans to tell Oberyn that Amory acted on his own, without orders, to gain favor from the new king, <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>, and hopes that Amory's recent brutal death will assuage Oberyn's need for justice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Later, to spite his father, Tyrion tells Oberyn that Amory Lorch did kill Rhaenys, but also that Gregor Clegane killed Elia and Aegon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a>, tells Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arys_Oakheart\" title=\"Arys Oakheart\">Arys Oakheart</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> that his charge, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Myrcella_Baratheon\" title=\"Myrcella Baratheon\">Myrcella Baratheon</a>, may be in danger. When Arys protests that only a beast would hurt a little girl, Doran reminds him of Amory and Rhaenys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>, Arya Stark sees people peacefully welcoming death at the <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_Black_and_White\" title=\"House of Black and White\">House of Black and White</a>, and recalls how Amory had begged in fear when thrown into the bear pit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a> reminds <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> about the <a href=\"/index.php/Curse_of_Harrenhal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Curse of Harrenhal\">curse of Harrenhal</a> and of the deaths of all who have held the castle recently, including Amory Lorch.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_21-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Roger_Hogg\" title=\"Roger Hogg\">Roger Hogg</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> how Amory attacked his towerhouse at <a href=\"/index.php/Sow%27s_Horn\" title=\"Sow&#39;s Horn\">Sow's Horn</a> and slaughtered his animals, even though he was sworn to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hayford\" title=\"House Hayford\">House Hayford</a>, who are sworn to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In Sunspear, <a href=\"/index.php/Ellaria_Sand\" title=\"Ellaria Sand\">Ellaria Sand</a> wishes for the end of the Martell hostilities against House Lannister, as all those who had a hand in the deaths of Elia and her children are dead, including Amory Lorch.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_22-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-22\">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Amory\">Quotes by Amory</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Amory\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Young boys and old men die the same.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Amory to <a href=\"/index.php/Yoren\" title=\"Yoren\">Yoren</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Amory\">Quotes about Amory</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Amory_Lorch&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Amory\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Vargo_Hoat\" title=\"Vargo Hoat\">Vargo Hoat</a> had Ser Amory torn apart by a <a href=\"/index.php/Bear\" title=\"Bear\">bear</a> after the <a href=\"/index.php/Fall_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Fall of Harrenhal\">fall of Harrenhal</a>. That ought to be sufficiently grisly to appease even <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I asked him afterward why it had required half a hundred thrusts to kill <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Rhaegar)\">a girl</a> of … two? Three? He said she'd kicked him and would not stop screaming. If Lorch had half the wits the gods gave a turnip, he would have calmed her with a few sweet words and used a soft silk pillow. The blood was in him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Only a beast would harm <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Rhaegar)\">a little girl</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Arys_Oakheart\" title=\"Arys Oakheart\">Arys Oakheart</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n